# GroveEngine clang-tidy — first static-analysis pass.
# Curated for BUG-FINDING, not style: real defect patterns (bugprone / clang-analyzer),
# avoidable copies (performance), and a few misc correctness checks. Style/modernize checks
# are intentionally OFF (low bug-signal, high noise) and can be layered in later.
# Run: clang-tidy -p build <file.cpp> (compile DB from the Ninja build, -DCMAKE_EXPORT_COMPILE_COMMANDS=ON).
# MinGW/Windows has no system clang-tidy -> pip wheel: `python -m pip install --user clang-tidy`.
# CROSS-TOOLCHAIN CAVEAT (Windows): a module TU whose include chain reaches bgfx's compat/mingw/sal.h makes the
# clang frontend recurse on that shim -> a SAL cascade that corrupts the std parse (std::string loses members)
# -> GARBAGE findings. Those TUs (SoundManager/VideoModule/BgfxRenderer) must be tidy'd on Linux (clean GCC
# toolchain, no MSVC SAL). Detail + the clean/tainted partition: docs/design/quality-hardening-handoff.md.
# Notable checks OFF (with reason):
#  - misc-const-correctness: floods (wants const on every lock_guard/local) — pedantic, not a bug-finder.
#  - bugprone-exception-escape: every hit here is a DESTRUCTOR; dtors are implicitly noexcept, so a throw
#    -> std::terminate is an acceptable FRANK failure. Wrapping dtors in try/catch would MASK errors
#    (against the no-silent-fallback doctrine), so we accept terminate over masking.
#  - performance-inefficient-string-concatenation: only path-building (`a + "/" + b`) — readability wins.
Checks: >
  -*,
  bugprone-*,
  performance-*,
  clang-analyzer-*,
  misc-*,
  -bugprone-easily-swappable-parameters,
  -bugprone-narrowing-conversions,
  -bugprone-exception-escape,
  -misc-no-recursion,
  -misc-non-private-member-variables-in-classes,
  -misc-include-cleaner,
  -misc-use-anonymous-namespace,
  -misc-const-correctness,
  -performance-avoid-endl,
  -performance-inefficient-string-concatenation

WarningsAsErrors: ''
# Only diagnose OUR headers (engine core + modules), never third-party under deps/ or external/.
HeaderFilterRegex: '(/include/grove/|/modules/|/src/).*'
FormatStyle: none
